					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640#post-3804815</guid>
				<title>Re: AUTHOR POST</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640/scp-3324#post-3804815</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 May 2018 19:35:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zzuxon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1496981</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>How the hell did the Foundation know this</p> </blockquote> <p>Towards the end, there's a short paragraph explaining how the Foundation discovered it.</p> <blockquote> <p>Oh god… did they make every D class pee into every sieve to ascertain if there are anymore anomalous instances???</p> </blockquote> <p>Well, I mean how else are they gonna do it? :)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640#post-3804811</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640/scp-3324#post-3804811</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 May 2018 19:30:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zzuxon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1496981</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Yeah, I love the idea that there could be enormous numbers of anomalies that people may never discover are actually anomalous because of a narrow activation trigger. Maybe such an anomaly is near you right now! OOOOHHHHH</p> <blockquote> <p>Okay, but real talk, I wanna know more about this. c.c</p> </blockquote> <p>You know, I originally wrote that part the way I did because I realized the comedic potential of alluding to some bizarre anomaly's properties without context, but I like what I came up with so much that I may actually write an SCP around it. So maybe you will know more about this in the future.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640#post-3804472</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640/scp-3324#post-3804472</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 May 2018 13:10:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is my favorite kind of SCP, the sort with such a ridiculously narrow parameter for activation that it's a miracle anyone found out it was anomalous in the first place. :D I also love the messing around with causality.</p> <blockquote> <p>SCP-████ underwent an Unwrapping Event and accidentally referred to itself in the third person, enabling SCP-████-1 to escape its containment chamber</p> </blockquote> <p>Okay, but real talk, I wanna know more about <em>this</em>. c.c</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640#post-3804376</guid>
				<title>Re: AUTHOR POST</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640/scp-3324#post-3804376</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 May 2018 11:20:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Eris Ashwood</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4059141</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I was about to ask, &quot;how the hell did someone come up with this?&quot; and then I read this&#8230;</p> <p>Anyway, How the hell did the Foundation know this and HOW the hell did they test every other sieve?</p> <p>Oh god&#8230; did they make every D class pee into every sieve to ascertain if there are anymore anomalous instances??? That is extremely disgusting, weird, and almost definitely what the foundation will do&#8230;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640#post-3804014</guid>
				<title>AUTHOR POST</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5964640/scp-3324#post-3804014</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 May 2018 03:11:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zzuxon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1496981</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>If you're interested in my other work, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/author-page-zzuxon">here is my author page</a><br /> My second SCP, let's hope it does at least as well as my first.</p> <p>Big thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weryllium" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2727655&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="Weryllium" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2727655)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weryllium" >Weryllium</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404533&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="Zyn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404533)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" >Zyn</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3440103&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="Captain Kirby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3440103)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" >Captain Kirby</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/whomstdveworm" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3953274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="whomstdveWorm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3953274)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/whomstdveworm" >whomstdveWorm</a></span> for discussing the concept with me.<br /> Big thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rubberchickenzilla" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3935783&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="rubberchickenzilla" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3935783)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rubberchickenzilla" >rubberchickenzilla</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ensophos" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1676981&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="Ensophos" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1676981)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ensophos" >Ensophos</a></span> for reviewing my draft and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stallmantic" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3472766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="Stallmantic" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3472766)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stallmantic" >Stallmantic</a></span> for helping me to determine if my usage of tachyons was plausible.</p> <p>But BIGGEST thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1554651552" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" >PeppersGhost</a></span> for the extremely detailed and insightful criticism, that has elevated my idea so much. Seriously, the ending Ghost helped me develop is 50x better than what I had in mind at first.</p> <p>This is inspired by my own experiences with kidney stones. I pee in a sieve (the very sieve in the image no less), because if the stone is causing me this much suffering, by god I get to look at it up close after it comes out! But, what if this strange behavior was a cause, rather than a symptom&#8230;</p> <p>EDIT: I took the photo. Fear not image license team!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
